== History ==
ActivePresenter has been developed by Atomi Systems Inc. since 2007. Version 1.0 was released in October 2008 and became available in online market six months later with three editions, including free of charge edition.
== Editions ==
Three editions are available at different prices, each having the capabilities of lower ones, plus added features.
The features of the various editions are compared in a table on the ActivePresenter Web site.
=== Free Edition ===
This edition is free of charge (freeware). It has most ActivePresenter features, but unrestricted export is limited to JPEG and PNG images, and WMV, AVI, MPEG4, WebM video formats, and SCORM. Other output formats are supported to demonstrate features, but an obtrusive watermark is added to output, and even with watermark it may not be used for any other purpose. Company moderator says: "The difference between editions is just available output format, forbidden output format will have a watermark and can only be used for feature demonstration and not for any other purposes (neither commercial nor non-commercial)." Pre-2012 versions added watermarks to all exported output.From 22 January 2012 the ActivePresenter website (available via ) announced "NO WATERMARK". Earlier versions did watermark exports.
=== Standard Edition ===
This edition additionally allows exporting to series of images, videos, flash videos and documents. User can also export to Microsoft PowerPoint presentations, Adobe Flash or HTML5 simulations with watermark on them.
=== Professional Edition ===
This additionally supports interactive simulations and quizzes in Adobe Flash .SWF or HTML5 output.